{:proof/problem-id "apm-a97A02", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (includes \\(f\\in L^p([0,1])\\), the averaging window, and the \\(h>0\\) parameter) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (doesn’t presume continuity or the norm bound; it states them as conclusions) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (encodes a substantive averaging lemma about \\(L^p\\) functions) · notes: Statement mirrors the exact averaging operator in the prompt and isolates a helper lemma on symmetric differences to justify continuity.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Show that local averages f_h(t) = (2h)^{-1} ∫_{t-h}^{t+h} f(x)\\,dx of an L^p([0,1]) function are continuous in t and satisfy the Hölder-bound |f_h(t)| ≤ (2h)^{-1/p}‖f‖_p.\"\n :terms [{:name \"normalized averaging kernel\"\n          :meaning \"g_{t,h}(x) = (2h)^{-1}mathbf 1_{[t-h,t+h]}(x) viewed inside L^q\"\n          :needed-because \"It rewrites f_h(t) as the L^p–L^q pairing ⟨f,g_{t,h}⟩ so continuity reduces to continuity of the kernel in L^q.\"}\n         {:name \"Hölder inequality\"\n          :meaning \"|∫ f g| ≤ ‖f‖_p ‖g‖_q with q the conjugate exponent\"\n          :needed-because \"It simultaneously yields the pointwise bound and controls the change in f_h when g_{t,h} varies.\"}\n         {:name \"symmetric-difference control\"\n          :meaning \"As t→s the sets [t-h,t+h] and [s-h,s+h] have symmetric-difference measure → 0\"\n          :needed-because \"This drives ‖g_{t,h}-g_{s,h}‖_q → 0 (or absolute continuity of ∫|f| for p=1), proving continuity.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"Holder inequality + continuity of indicator kernels in L^q\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Stage 1 discussion of symmetric differences\"\n             :why-this-now \"Bound |f_h(t)-f_h(s)| by ‖f‖_p times the L^q-norm of the difference of kernels, showing continuity.\"\n             :lean-target \"avg_kernel_continuous\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Needs lemmas about indicator symmetric differences and Hölder already in Mathlib.\"}\n            {:id :s2\n             :formal-dependency \"Holder inequality\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Stage 1 Hölder bound computation\"\n             :why-this-now \"Compute ‖g_{t,h}‖_q explicitly to obtain |f_h(t)| ≤ (2h)^{-1/p}‖f‖_p.\"\n             :lean-target \"avg_kernel_bound\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Pure computation once the kernel is in L^q.\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done :stage2 :done :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:main-claim {:informal-claim \"For every 1 ≤ p < ∞, every f ∈ L^p([0,1]), and every fixed h>0, the averaging map t ↦ (1/(2h))∫_{t-h}^{t+h} f(x)dx is continuous on [0,1] and satisfies |f_h(t)| ≤ (2h)^{-1/p}‖f‖_p.\"\n             :formal-name \"avg_local_continuous_bound\"\n             :formal-target \"∀ {p : ℝ≥0∞} (hp : 1 ≤ p) (hp' : p < ∞)\n    {f : ℝ → ℂ}, MemLp f p (Measure.restrict volume (Set.Icc (0 : ℝ) 1)) →\n    ∀ {h : ℝ}, 0 < h →\n      Continuous fun t ↦ (1 / (2 * h)) * ∫ x, (Set.indicator (Set.Icc (t - h) (t + h)) (fun y => f y)) x ∂volume ∧\n      ∀ t ∈ Set.Icc (0 : ℝ) 1,\n        ‖(1 / (2 * h)) * ∫ x, (Set.indicator (Set.Icc (t - h) (t + h)) (fun y => f y)) x ∂volume‖ ≤ (2 * h) ^ (-1 / p.toReal) * ‖f‖_{Lp p}.\"\n             :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                            :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                            :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                            :notes \"This Lean target literally encodes continuity plus the Hölder bound for the normalized average operator.\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"avg_local_continuous_bound\"\n              :formal-statement \"...same as above...\"\n              :informal-clause \"Exactly the sentence asserting continuity and the Hölder bound.\"\n              :role :main-theorem}\n             {:formal-name \"indicator_symmetric_difference_Lq_tendsto\"\n              :formal-statement \"∀ h>0, ‖(2h)^{-1}1_{[t-h,t+h]} - (2h)^{-1}1_{[s-h,s+h]}‖_q → 0 as t→s.\"\n              :informal-clause \"Used inside Stage 1 to turn symmetric-difference control into continuity of f_h.\"\n              :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (explicitly references \\(f\\in L^p([0,1])\\), the averaging window, the continuity goal, and the Hölder bound) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (continuity and the bound are conclusions, not hypotheses) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (states a substantive theorem about averaging operators that stands on its own) · notes: Added a concrete helper lemma about indicator kernels tending to each other in \\(L^q\\), matching the Stage 1 symmetric-difference idea.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Prove that the local average f_h(t) = (2h)^{-1} ∫_{t-h}^{t+h} f(x) dx of any f ∈ L^p([0,1]) (1 ≤ p < ∞) is continuous in t and obeys the bound |f_h(t)| ≤ (2h)^{-1/p}‖f‖_p.\"\n :terms [{:name \"averaging kernel\"\n          :meaning \"g_{t,h} = (2h)^{-1} · 1_{[t-h,t+h]} viewed as an L^q function (q the Hölder conjugate).\"\n          :needed-because \"Expresses f_h(t) as the L^p–L^q dual pairing ⟨f, g_{t,h}⟩ so we can apply Hölder and continuity of kernels.\"}\n         {:name \"Hölder inequality\"\n          :meaning \"|∫ fg| ≤ ‖f‖_p ‖g‖_q for conjugate exponents.\"\n          :needed-because \"Gives both the claimed bound on f_h(t) and the Lipschitz control once g_{t,h} varies with t.\"}\n         {:name \"symmetric-difference estimate\"\n          :meaning \"m([t-h,t+h] △ [s-h,s+h]) → 0 as t→s.\"\n          :needed-because \"Shows ‖g_{t,h} - g_{s,h}‖_q → 0, hence |f_h(t)-f_h(s)| → 0 via Hölder.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"Hölder inequality and continuity of indicator kernels in L^q\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Stage 1 symmetric-difference argument\"\n             :why-this-now \"Bounding |f_h(t)-f_h(s)| by ‖f‖_p · ‖g_{t,h}-g_{s,h}‖_q gives continuity once the kernel difference shrinks.\"\n             :lean-target \"avg_kernel_continuous\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Needs lemmas about measure of symmetric differences and Hölder, both in Mathlib.\"}\n            {:id :s2\n             :formal-dependency \"Hölder inequality\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Stage 1 computation of the norm bound\"\n             :why-this-now \"Computing ‖g_{t,h}‖_q = (2h)^{(1/q)-1} yields |f_h(t)| ≤ (2h)^{-1/p}‖f‖_p.\"\n             :lean-target \"avg_kernel_bound\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Direct algebra once g_{t,h} is in L^q.\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done :stage2 :done :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:main-claim {:informal-claim \"For every 1 ≤ p < ∞, every f ∈ L^p([0,1]), and every h>0, the average f_h(t) = (2h)^{-1}∫_{t-h}^{t+h} f(x)dx is continuous on [0,1] and satisfies |f_h(t)| ≤ (2h)^{-1/p}‖f‖_p.\"\n             :formal-name \"avg_local_continuous_bound\"\n             :formal-target \"∀ {p : ℝ≥0∞} (hp₁ : 1 ≤ p) (hpfin : p < ∞)\n  {f : ℝ → ℝ}, MemLp f p (Measure.restrict volume (Set.Icc (0 : ℝ) 1)) →\n  ∀ {h : ℝ}, 0 < h →\n    (Continuous fun t : ℝ => (1 / (2 * h)) * ∫ x, (Set.indicator (Set.Icc (t - h) (t + h)) f) x ∂volume) ∧\n    ∀ {t : ℝ}, t ∈ Set.Icc (0 : ℝ) 1 →\n      ‖(1 / (2 * h)) * ∫ x, (Set.indicator (Set.Icc (t - h) (t + h)) f) x ∂volume‖ ≤ (2 * h) ^ (-1 / p.toReal) * snorm f p (Measure.restrict volume (Set.Icc (0 : ℝ) 1)).\"\n             :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                            :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                            :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                            :notes \"Statement matches the averaging operator continuity and Hölder bound literally.\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"avg_local_continuous_bound\"\n              :formal-statement \"same as formal-target\"\n              :informal-clause \"Certifies the headline claim that f_h is continuous and bounded.\"\n              :role :main-theorem}\n             {:formal-name \"indicator_kernel_tendsto\"\n              :formal-statement \"∀ h > 0, Tendsto (fun t => indicator (Icc (t - h) (t + h)) (fun x => (2 * h)⁻¹))\n                                   (nhds s)\n                                   (nhds (indicator (Icc (s - h) (s + h)) (fun x => (2 * h)⁻¹))) in L^q norm.\"\n              :informal-clause \"Provides the continuity of kernels needed in Stage 1.\"\n              :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\nHere’s the completed write-up:\n\n- Stage 1 of `execute.md` now contains the full reader-facing discussion: why the problem is tricky, the averaging-kernel insight, a detailed proof using Hölder plus symmetric differences, and a “what connects’’ field kit.\n- Stage 2 records the key lemmas (“averaging kernel in \\(L^q\\)” and “kernel continuity via symmetric difference’’) with their formal targets, matching the updated `proof-plan.edn` and the aligned `formal-alignment.edn`.\n- Stage 3 documents the Lean status: I planned to formalize the kernel as an `Lp` function and use Hölder, but I’m blocked because Mathlib lacks a lemma showing that sliding indicators are continuous in `Lp`; finishing the proof just requires that ingredient.\n- Stage 4 reconciles the informal and formal stories.\n\nThe changelog now logs workspace init plus Stage 1/Stage 2 completions and the Stage 3 blocker (with `:sorry? true`).", :proof/extraction {:phases {}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :partial, :phase-count 0, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :proof/frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A97A02/Apm_v2_a97A02_1775003733088", :frame/id "apm-v2-a97A02-1775003733088", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T00:35:33.111996Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.A97A02.Apm_v2_a97A02_1775003733088"